hints.description: This company develops and sells technologies used by law enforcement and military agencies worldwide. Their offerings include body-worn cameras, digital evidence management software, and electric control devices designed to reduce officer use-of-force incidents. Founder Rick Smith started the business in his garage after witnessing a police officer use a Taser on a suspect and believing there was a better way to de-escalate situations.
hints.funFact1: Initially, the company was known as *****, reflecting its focus on developing a less-lethal alternative to traditional restraints. The name was later changed to better reflect the broader range of products and services offered.
hints.funFact2: ***** has a unique employee profit-sharing program where employees receive a portion of the company’s profits, regardless of their role or seniority, fostering a strong sense of ownership and shared success.
